Tommy A. Valenta  Director, American Excelsior, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships68--
Background

		Mr. Tommy A. Valenta, also known as Tom, served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Chaparral Steel Company from July 29, 2005 to September 2007. Mr. Valenta served as an Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer - Steel of Texas Industries Inc. from 1998 to July 29, 2005. He joined TXI in 1970 and served as Vice-President of Concrete, Transportation and Cement Marketing from 1992 to 1998. He served as General Manager, Division Vice President for ... Aggregate Development, North Texas Ready-Mix, Transportation, Cement Marketing and Concrete at Chaparral Steel Co. He served as an Executive Vice President of Steel at Chaparral Steel Co. since 1998. Mr. Valenta serves as a Director of American Excelsior Company. He served as a Director of HollyFrontier Corporation since February 24, 2010 until March 7, 2017. He served as a Director of Chaparral Steel Company Inc from February 2005 to September 2007. He serves as Director and Chairman of Executive Committee for Chaparral Steel Company Inc. Throughout his career, he served as a Director for various industry associations including the National Ready-Mix Concrete Association, American Institute of Steel Construction and the Steel Manufacturers Association. Mr. Valenta is on the board of directors of the Circle Ten Council of the Boy Scouts of America and Cashiers Community Fund and serves as President for the Episcopal Diocese of Dallas. Mr. Valenta received his MBA from Southern Methodist University in Dallas in 1994.Read Full Background




