HollyFrontier Corporation Statement on the Passing of Board Member, Tommy A. Valenta

 DALLAS--(BUSINESS WIRE)--

      HollyFrontier Corporation (NYSE: HFC) ("HollyFrontier") is sad to

      announce the passing of Tommy A. Valenta.

    

Mr. Valenta served on the Board of Directors for HollyFrontier since

      2010. He was an independent director and a member of the Audit and

      Environmental, Health, Safety, and Public Policy Committees.

    


      "We are deeply saddened by the passing of our colleague and friend,"

      said George Damiris, Chief Executive Officer and President. "On behalf

      of the entire HollyFrontier team, we extend our deepest condolences to

      his family and friends. Tommy's vast experience and principled guidance

      were invaluable to his fellow directors, our management team and our

      company. He touched so many lives as a willing mentor, a selfless and

      loyal friend, and an avid community supporter. We will greatly miss him

      and his contributions."

    

About HollyFrontier Corporation:


HollyFrontier Corporation, headquartered in Dallas, Texas, is an

      independent petroleum refiner and marketer that produces high value

      light products such as gasoline, diesel fuel, jet fuel and other

      specialty products. HollyFrontier operates through its subsidiaries a

      135,000 barrels per stream day ("bpsd") refinery located in El Dorado,

      Kansas, a 125,000 bpsd refinery in Tulsa, Oklahoma, a 100,000 bpsd

      refinery located in Artesia, New Mexico, a 52,000 bpsd refinery located

      in Cheyenne, Wyoming and a 45,000 bpsd refinery in Woods Cross, Utah.

      HollyFrontier markets its refined products principally in the Southwest

      U.S., the Rocky Mountains extending into the Pacific Northwest and in

      other neighboring Plains states. In addition, HollyFrontier, through its

      subsidiary, owns Petro-Canada Lubricants Inc., whose Mississauga,

      Ontario facility produces 15,600 barrels per day of base oils and other

      specialized lubricant products, and owns a 37% interest (including a 2%

      general partner interest) in Holly Energy Partners, L.P.



      Information about the Company may be found on its website at www.hollyfrontier.com.

    


View source version on businesswire.com: http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170214005218/en/

HollyFrontier CorporationJulia Heidenreich, 214-954-6510Vice

      President, Investor RelationsorCraig Biery, 214-954-6510Manager,

      Investor Relations

    
Source: HollyFrontier Corporation

